  "prompt": "How should I prepare for Google Geo Engineering Program Manager India interview?",
  "response": "To prepare for a Google Geo Engineering Program Manager interview in India, here are some key strategies:\n\nTechnical Preparation:\n1. Understand Google Maps/Geo products deeply\n- Familiarity with Google Maps, Google Earth\n- Knowledge of geospatial technologies\n- Understanding of mapping infrastructure\n\nProduct Management Skills:\n1. Study Google's product management principles\n2. Practice product sense questions\n3. Demonstrate ability to:\n- Define product vision\n- Prioritize features\n- Analyze user needs\n- Create product roadmaps\n\nTechnical Background:\n1. Understand geospatial engineering concepts\n2. Basic knowledge of:\n- GIS technologies\n- Mapping algorithms\n- Location-based services\n- Spatial data processing\n\nInterview Preparation:\n1. Practice behavioral questions\n2. Prepare STAR method answers\n3. Research Google's culture and values\n4. Review past project experiences\n5. Demonstrate leadership and collaboration skills\n\nTechnical Interview Topics:\n- Product design scenarios\n- Technical problem-solving\n- Geospatial data challenges\n- Scaling mapping solutions\n\nSoft Skills:\n- Communication clarity\n- Strategic thinking\n- Cross-functional collaboration\n- Innovation mindset\n\nRecommended Resources:\n- Google's engineering blog\n- Cracking the PM Interview book\n- LeetCode/HackerRank practice\n- Mock interviews",
